cent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io', 'exploit-db.com'], 'email-addr': ['disclosure@vulncheck.com'], 'url': ['http://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/50261', 'http://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/argus-surveillance-dvr-unquoted-service-path-privilege-escalation', 'https://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/50261', 'https://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/argus-surveillance-dvr-unquoted-service-path-privilege-escalation'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2021-47945']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2021-47944 - memono Notepad 4.2 Denial of Service via Buffer Overflow', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 10 May 2026 13:16:30 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2021-47944', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['memono Notepad 4.2 contains a denial of service vulnerability that allows attackers to crash the application by pasting excessively long character buffers into note fields. Attackers can generate a payload containing 350000 repeated characters and paste it twice into a new note to trigger an application crash on iOS devices.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2021-47944vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2021-47944weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io', 'exploit-db.com'], 'email-addr': ['disclosure@vulncheck.com'], 'url': ['http://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/49977', 'http://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/memono-notepad-denial-of-service-via-buffer-overflow', 'https://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/49977', 'https://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/memono-notepad-denial-of-service-via-buffer-overflow'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2021-47944']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2021-47943 - TextPattern CMS 4.8.7 Remote Code Execution via File Upload', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 10 May 2026 13:16:30 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2021-47943', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['TextPattern CMS 4.8.7 contains a remote code execution vulnerability that allows authenticated attackers to execute arbitrary commands by uploading malicious PHP files through the file upload functionality. Attackers can upload a PHP shell via the Files section in the content area and execute commands by accessing the uploaded file at /textpattern/files/ with GET parameters passed to the system function.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2021-47943vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2021-47943weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observabl