 exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io', 'exploit-db.com'], 'email-addr': ['disclosure@vulncheck.com'], 'ipv4-addr': ['1.5.7.3'], 'url': ['http://modalsurvey.pantherius.com/', 'http://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/50269', 'http://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/wordpress-plugin-survey-poll-sql-injection-via-sss-params', 'https://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/50269', 'https://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/wordpress-plugin-survey-poll-sql-injection-via-sss-params'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2021-47941']}}, {'title': 'CVE-2021-47940 - WordPress Download From Files 1.48 Arbitrary File Upload', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 10 May 2026 13:16:30 +0000', 'source': 'https://cvefeed.io/vuln/detail/CVE-2021-47940', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': ['WordPress Plugin Download From Files version 1.48 and earlier contains an arbitrary file upload vulnerability that allows unauthenticated attackers to upload malicious files by exploiting the AJAX fileupload action. Attackers can send POST requests to the admin-ajax.php endpoint with the download_from_files_617_fileupload action, manipulating the allowExt parameter to bypass file type restrictions and upload executable files like PHP shells to the web root.', 'The following products are affected byCVE-2021-47940vulnerability. Even ifcvefeed.iois aware of the exact versions of the products that are affected, the information is not represented in the table below.', 'Common Attack Pattern Enumeration and Classification (CAPEC) stores attack patterns, which are descriptions of the common attributes and approaches employed by adversaries to exploit theCVE-2021-47940weaknesses.', 'We scan GitHub repositories to detect new proof-of-concept exploits. Following list is a collection of public exploits and proof-of-concepts, which have been published on GitHub (sorted by the most recently updated).', "Vulnerability history details can be useful for understanding the evolution of a vulnerability, and for identifying the most recent changes that may impact the vulnerability's severity, exploitability, or other characteristics."], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cvefeed.io', 'exploit-db.com'], 'email-addr': ['disclosure@vulncheck.com'], 'url': ['http://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/50287', 'http://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/wordpress-download-from-files-arbitrary-file-upload', 'https://wordpress.org/plugins/download-from-files/', 'https://www.exploit-db.com/exploits/50287', 'https://www.vulncheck.com/advisories/wordpress-download-from-files-arbitrary-file-upload'], 'vulnerability': ['CVE-2021-47940']}}, {'title': 'A government contractor hired twin brothers who were convicted felons. A year later, it regretted it.', 'publication_date': 'Sun, 10 May 2026 20:35:49 +0000', 'source': 'https://databreaches.net/2026/05/10/a-government-contractor-hired-twin-brothers-who-were-convicted-felons-a-year-later-they-regretted-it/?pk_campaign=feed&pk_kwd=a-government-contractor-hired-twin-brothers-who-were-convicted-felons-a-year-later-they-regretted-it', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['databreaches.net']}}, {'title': "The ACS is still looking into this, but the potential impact for a whole lot of IT professionals is pretty nasty.I suspect this hack's going to be making the news for some time.#shinyhunters #databreach #cybersecurity https://www.cyberdaily.au/security/13572-exclusive-australian-computer-society-investigating-possible-breach-after-shinyhunters-hack-claims", 'publication_date': 'Mon, 11 May 2026 00:59:50 +0000', 'source': 'https://mastodon.social/@David_Hollingworth/116553131811320692', 'source_type': "['']", 'source_level': 2, 'text': [], 'observables': {'domain-name': ['cyberdaily.au'], 'email-addr': ['David_Hollingworth@mastodon.social']}}, {'title': 'Healthcare technology company RXNT has reported a major data breach affecting patient data. The incident involved unauthorized access to its syste